      "description": "Predicted NIH values from the power-law damage integral compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements at five flow-speed operating points. Predicted RH values within 15% of measured values at four of five points; one outlier at low-flow high-speed condition attributed to measurement uncertainty. The power-law model is applied assuming IID linear damage accumulation across fluid parcels; this precondition is documented in the model theory guide and is accepted without verification.",
