      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The power-law hemolysis model and SST k-omega turbulence closure are appropriate for the flow physics present in the CPB pump COU. Model form uncertainty is acknowledged and bounded.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage integral is the standard hemolysis model for CFD-based pump assessment and is referenced in FDA guidance. The model is theoretically grounded in the assumption that erythrocyte damage accumulates as a linear, path-independent integral over fluid parcel trajectories — requiring that damage contributions across sub-volumes are independent and identically distributed. This IID linearity precondition is explicitly stated in the model theory documentation and is a necessary condition for the volume-averaged damage integral to be valid. The precondition is accepted as plausible for the nominal operating range and is not further examined in this assessment. SST k-omega turbulence model selected for its established performance in rotating machinery flows with adverse pressure gradients."
    },
